He made you promise. didn't he?

930
01:57:29.943 --> 01:57:34.526
To stay away from me. So I'd be safe.

931
01:58:00.518 --> 01:58:03.656
- What a pretty girl.
- Yeah...

932
01:58:03.931 --> 01:58:08.197
- that's what uncle Ben said.
- Did you ask her out?

933
01:58:11.973 --> 01:58:13.673
Why?

934
01:58:14.002 --> 01:58:15.871
I can't.

935
01:58:16.683 --> 01:58:18.352
Why?

936
01:58:20.741 --> 01:58:23.297
I'm just no good for her.

937
01:58:25.655 --> 01:58:30.133
Peter Parker. if there's
one thing you are. it's good.

938
01:58:30.257 --> 01:58:33.017
If anyone has a problem
with that can talk to me.

939
01:58:50.855 --> 01:58:55.534
<i>Peter. I know things have
been difficult lately.</i>

940
01:58:55.752 --> 01:59:00.608
<i>and I'm sorry about that.
I think I know what you're feeling.</i>

941
01:59:01.212 --> 01:59:07.983
<i>Ever since you were a little boy.
you've been living with so many unresolved things.</i>

942
01:59:09.651 --> 01:59:12.479
<i>Well. take it from an old man.</i>

943
01:59:12.851 --> 01:59:15.767
<i>those things send us down the road.</i>

944
01:59:15.895 --> 01:59:17.846
<i>and make us who we are.</i>

945
01:59:18.437 --> 01:59:22.027
<i>And if anyone's destined
for greatness.</i>

946
01:59:22.136 --> 01:59:24.024
<i> it's you son.</ I>

947
01:59:24.315 --> 01:59:26.898
<i>You owe the world your gifts.</i>

948
01:59:27.218 --> 01:59:30.603
<i> you just have to figure out how to use them.</ i>

949
01:59:30.777 --> 01:59:36.065
<i>And know that wherever they take you. we'll always be here.</i>

950
01:59:37.596 --> 01:59:43.472
<i>So come on home Peter.
You're my hero and I love you.</i>

951
01:59:52.338 --> 01:59:55.423
- Hello Parker.
- Hey. how's it going?

952
01:59:55.595 --> 01:59:57.631
You coming along man?

953
01:59:59.620 --> 02:00:01.352
That's a cool shirt.

954
02:00:02.223 --> 02:00:06.670
Yeah. dude's crazy. But chicks dig him.

955
02:00:21.744 --> 02:00:23.998
I had a professor once who liked to
tell his students that there were only

956
02:00:24.033 --> 02:00:28.167
ten different plots in all of fiction.

957
02:00:28.869 --> 02:00:30.980
Well I'm here to tell you he
was wrong. 

958
02:00:31.058 --> 02:00:35.095
there is only one. Who am I?

959
02:00:35.662 --> 02:00:39.048
Mr. Parker. tardy again.

960
02:00:40.572 --> 02:00:42.622
Well. at least we can
always count on you.

961
02:00:42.721 --> 02:00:45.180
Sorry Miss Ritter. it won't
happen again. I promise.

962
02:00:45.286 --> 02:00:47.714
Don't make promises you
can't keep. Mr. Parker.

963
02:00:49.944 --> 02:00:52.473
But those are the best kind.

964
02:00:52.508 --> 02:00:56.591
OK class. open your books.
let's begin on page 1.

966
02:02:46.659 --> 02:02:49.040
Hello doctor.

967
02:02:49.120 --> 02:02:51.928
- Did you tell the boy?
- Tell him what?

968
02:02:52.008 --> 02:02:56.189
Did you tell the boy the
truth about his father?

969
02:02:57.217 --> 02:03:00.337
- No.
- That's very good.

970
02:03:00.460 --> 02:03:03.080
We will let him be for now.

971
02:03:03.566 --> 02:03:05.565
You should leave him alone!
